@1928_main
new-page: true
go-to: main if difficulty >= 0; main.main_easy if difficulty < 0

= 4000

It is a dark time for Melinian socialism. The past decade has seen the already minor and inefficient force splinter following the Great Schism, wherein, under the compulsion of the Meline Planetary Government following its unanimous decision, and the enforcement of this compulsion by Meline Central's eager police forces, the party was forced to expel all dissidents and their sympathizers, a fact which deprived the anti-corporate struggle of the unifying banner it could have had.

But, the decade begins anew. Even as Monroe Corporation appears more entrenched than ever, the party retains the opportunity to rectify its mistakes.